&gt; The dropoff_age is a way to penalize stagnation.  It does not kill of species
&gt; after e.g. 50 generations;  rather, it kills the species off after 50
&gt; generations of *stagnation*, which means lack of improvement in maximum
&gt; fitness.  The idea is, if a species has not improved in a long time, then the
&gt; investment that it represents in CPU resources may not be worth it, so it can
&gt; be caused to die out by massively penalizing it.  Of course, using this
&gt; technique is optional and up to the experimenter.

Hi Ken-

A quick and minor question: out of curiosity, how does this technique behave
if the population as a whole has stagnated for more than 50 generations
(which is very common at the end of long runs).

-jeff

